🧠 Introduction

In this room, I learned the basics of networking, which is a very important part of cybersecurity. Before learning hacking or security tools, understanding how networks work is essential. 🔐

🌐 What is Networking?

Networking means connecting multiple devices so they can communicate with each other. These devices share data using protocols.

🧩 OSI Model Explained

The OSI model helps us understand how data moves from one system to another. Each layer has a specific role, from sending raw bits to displaying data to the user.

👉 Example: When you open a website, data passes through all 7 layers.

🌍 TCP/IP Model

This model is used in real-world networking. It combines multiple OSI layers into fewer layers, making it simpler and more practical.

🔢 IP Addressing

Every device on a network has an IP address. It works like a home address, helping data reach the correct destination.

IPv4 → Limited addresses
IPv6 → Large number of addresses
🌐 DNS

Instead of remembering IP addresses, we use domain names. DNS converts these names into IP addresses.

👉 Without DNS, we would need to remember numbers instead of website names.

🔌 Networking Devices
Router → Connects different networks
Switch → Connects devices in a network
Firewall → Protects network from threats
